<subSubSection id="1A2043B9D4AC06D0B1925CF01E7A8A2B" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="basionym">
<paragraph id="A55E7C09E86D67C8A403B5536B0E70CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Basionym.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8911B4AD292879EBF9F408199F5CC1BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="9D49FCF1C178B986745FA4BEA6D72CCD" authority="" authorityName="I.V.Makarova" authorityYear="1979" class="Mediophyceae" family="Thalassiosiraceae" genus="Thalassiosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thalassiosira proschkinae" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="proschkinae">
<emphasis id="A4CDCFBC48E515752B2DBDEE9C1304CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Thalassiosira proschkinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I.V. Makarova in Makarova, Genkal and Kuzmin, Bot. Zhurn. 64(7): 922, pl. 1, figs 1-7. 1979.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D8CF72A25E8F46450EEA2CE195D02F09" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph id="3EE014B5A4FF0CD7C3971D4E85725D0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E63F45A178D278EF0D92A51487BD65CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
The frustule is cylindrical, valve flat, diameter 3.8-4.9 
<normalizedToken id="6E8AE86913D01352A79B56D7B54D9F98" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, areolae polygonal, in quantities 25 in 10 
<normalizedToken id="432B32C5357DE02C3F23F4B872F641A1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, near centre of a valve, the central process and rimoportula are located (Figs 
<figureCitation id="2A136EA168B9BA6429A1F2268AF7B5DB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. SEM (A, B and E-H) and LM (C, D) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: A-D Pleurosira laevis A, C valve views with arrows shown the ocelli B girdle view E Conticribra weissflogii, valve view with arrows shown central and marginal fultoportulae F Thalassiosira incerta, valve view with arrow shown central fultoportulae G Thalassiosira faurii, valve view H Minidiscus proschkinae, valve view with arrow in the centre shown central fultoportula, and closer to the edge - rimoportula. Scale bars: 10 μm (C-G); 30 μm (A); 50 μm (B); 3 μm (H)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545736" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">4H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="EC4030BA90482D7CA62D5DBB4EACAC47" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. SEM images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city (A, B, E-H valve views, C, D girdle views): A Minidiscus proschkinae with arrows showing rimoportula and marginal fultoportula B-D Skeletonema subsalsum with arrows showing marginal fultoportulae E Stephanodiscus hantzschii with arrow shown spines F Stephanodiscus makarovae with arrows showing marginal and central fultoportulae G, H Stephanodiscus minutulus with arrows showing spines and central fultoportula. Scale bars: 3 μm (A); 4 μm (B, F, H); 5 μm (C, D, G); 10 μm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545737" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D665CC3C8CA36FD026FFCCD5E7ABB5A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="3C63F3B08ADDA083DBA20768A825637E" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD53700BA9EA162C93ACAFBF30CBC783" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
This planktonic taxon has been mainly found in estuaries characterized by low salinity and high turbulence, and in seas, but also in freshwaters and may be a halophile indicator (
<bibRefCitation id="9E471D399221F837DE3478AB5C3170A3" author="Makarova, IV" journalOrPublisher="] Akademiya NAUK SSSR, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B87" refString="Makarova, IV, 1988. . Diatomovye vodorosli morei SSSR: Rod Thalassiosira Cl. [Diatoms of the seas of the USSR: genus Thalassiosira Cl.] Akademiya NAUK SSSR, Leningrad" title=". Diatomovye vodorosli morei SSSR: Rod Thalassiosira Cl. [Diatoms of the seas of the USSR: genus Thalassiosira Cl." year="1988">Makarova 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4050CF6A94B274812C2C96A3E9DA27AA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0181980" author="Park, JS" journalOrPublisher="British Phycological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B100" refString="Park, JS, Jung, SW, Ki, JS, Guo, R, Kim, HJ, Lee, K-W, Lee, JH, 2017a. Transfer of the small diatoms Thalassiosira proschkinae and T. spinulata to the genus Minidiscus and their taxonomic re-description. PLoS ONE 12(9): e0181980. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0181980" title="Transfer of the small diatoms Thalassiosira proschkinae and T. spinulata to the genus Minidiscus and their taxonomic re-description. PLoS ONE 12 (9): e 0181980." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0181980" year="2017 a">Park et al. 2017a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="017AA2A2DD9DBD7E7F742CEE4AA8F01F" author="Barinova, SS" journalOrPublisher="University of Haifa Publisher, Haifa, Kyiv" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B6" refString="Barinova, SS, Bilous, OP, Tsarenko, PM, 2019. Algal indication of water bodies in Ukraine: methods and perspectives. University of Haifa Publisher, Haifa, Kyiv" title="Algal indication of water bodies in Ukraine: methods and perspectives." year="2019">Barinova et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CEE00F7F42EF983ECAD0A563B499E179" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="ABFDE141047104F9C91B766EB00C23E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9CBD2715F027820BC61D861A4FCBB44" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Valves were found in benthic samples in Mykolaiv city of the Southern Bug River and downriver (Table 
<tableCitation id="567126C02F382D0237C1503B8ADFD1F8" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). For Ukrainian territory it was recorded for estuaries of the Black Sea and nearshore regions (
<bibRefCitation id="447B11FDFF215686D12DC36DC225E4CF" author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E6E61D38C32755995A80FD514A808815" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Hydrobiological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="38 - 49" refId="B42" refString="Genkal, SI, Terenko, LM, 2014. New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Black Sea. Hydrobiological Journal 50 (2): 38 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" title="New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Black Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" volume="50" year="2014">Genkal and Terenko 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C57C04623A78A83B0B762C4AFD677D7F" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="E71D4895951984BA0C488DC52844473F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Thalassiosiraceae" genus="Minidiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Minidiscus proschkinae" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="proschkinae">
<emphasis id="BB48B8235F79F752D875E1CC308F79AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Minidiscus proschkinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed across estuaries and seacoasts of Europe (Germany, Great Britain, Netherlands, Russia, Ukraine), Asia (Azerbaijan, China), Argentina; Azov Sea, Baltic Sea, Caspian Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="730D5395889C0D472CD1DC80439E6C45" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0181980" author="Park, JS" journalOrPublisher="British Phycological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B100" refString="Park, JS, Jung, SW, Ki, JS, Guo, R, Kim, HJ, Lee, K-W, Lee, JH, 2017a. Transfer of the small diatoms Thalassiosira proschkinae and T. spinulata to the genus Minidiscus and their taxonomic re-description. PLoS ONE 12(9): e0181980. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0181980" title="Transfer of the small diatoms Thalassiosira proschkinae and T. spinulata to the genus Minidiscus and their taxonomic re-description. PLoS ONE 12 (9): e 0181980." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0181980" year="2017 a">Park et al. 2017a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
